"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Real-Time Turbopuffer Indexing via Cloudflare Queue\n\n## Context\n\nCheckpoints are indexed in Turbopuffer for search. Currently indexing only happens via the backfill script. When new checkpoints arrive via GitHub webhooks, they need to be indexed in Turbopuffer in real-time. The indexing must be async and non-blocking to the webhook processing pipeline, using Cloudflare Queues (already set up for other flows).\n\n## Approach\n\nAdd a new `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` Cloudflare Queue. After checkpoint data is upserted into PlanetScale (in both `processSessionsPushEvent` and `processCommitPushEvent`), send a lightweight message to the queue. A new queue consumer fetches checkpoint data from PlanetScale, embeds search text via OpenAI, and upserts vectors to Turbopuffer.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | **Create** | Message type, type guard, batch processor |\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Modify** | Add `indexCheckpoints()` function (embed + upsert) |\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue` |\n| `api/wrangler.jsonc` | **Modify** | Add queue producer + consumer (staging & production) |\n| `api/src/index.ts` | **Modify** | Add queue consumer branch for search index messages |\n| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | **Modify** | Enqueue after upsert in both push event handlers |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. Search Index Queue (`api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`)\n\nFollow existing `RepoSyncMessage` / `UserRepoSyncMessage` pattern from `repo-sync-queue.ts` and `user-repo-sync.ts`.\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SearchIndexMessage {\n  repoId: string;\n  checkpointIds: string[];\n  queuedAt: string;\n}\n\nexport function isSearchIndexMessage(msg: unknown): msg is SearchIndexMessage { ... }\n\nexport async function processSearchIndexBatch(\n  batch: MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\n  env: Env,\n): Promise<void> { ... }\n```\n\n**Batch processor flow per message:**\n1. Early return if `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY` missing — `msg.ack()` + warning log\n2. Fetch checkpoint + commit data from PlanetScale via `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\n3. Build search text per checkpoint (same format as `buildSearchText()` in backfill script)\n4. Call `indexCheckpoints()` from turbopuffer.ts\n5. Success → `msg.ack()`, transient failure → `msg.retry()`\n\nLogging follows `[search-index-queue]` prefix pattern, with batch metrics matching `repo-sync-queue.ts`.\n\n### 2. Turbopuffer Indexing Function (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\n\nAdd `indexCheckpoints()` alongside existing `searchCheckpoints()`:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function indexCheckpoints(\n  turbopufferApiKey: string,\n  openaiApiKey: string,\n  repoId: string,\n  checkpoints: Array<{\n    checkpoint_id: string;\n    branch: string | null;\n    agent: string | null;\n    commit_author_username: string | null;\n    created_at: string | null;\n    commit_sha: string | null;\n    commit_message: string | null;\n    prompt: string | null;\n    files_touched: string[] | null;\n  }>,\n): Promise<number>\n```\n\n- Build search text: `Prompt: ...\\nCommit: ...\\nFiles: ...` (same as backfill `buildSearchText()`)\n- Embed via OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dims) — batch all texts in one call\n- Upsert to Turbopuffer `POST /v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repoId}/upsert` with same attributes as backfill\n- Use deterministic numeric IDs from checkpoint_id hash (consistent with potential re-indexing)\n- Returns count of successfully indexed checkpoints\n\n### 3. Env Binding (`api/src/env.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nSEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue;  // Optional — indexing skipped if not configured\n```\n\nOptional so existing environments without the queue continue working.\n\n### 4. Wrangler Config (`api/wrangler.jsonc`)\n\n**Staging (default):**\n```jsonc\n// In producers array:\n{ \"binding\": \"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\", \"queue\": \"partialto-api-search-index\" }\n// In consumers array:\n{ \"queue\": \"partialto-api-search-index\", \"max_retries\": 3, \"max_batch_size\": 10, \"max_batch_timeout\": 5 }\n```\n\n**Production (`env.production`):**\n```jsonc\n// In producers array:\n{ \"binding\": \"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\", \"queue\": \"entireio-api-search-index\" }\n// In consumers array:\n{ \"queue\": \"entireio-api-search-index\", \"max_retries\": 3, \"max_batch_size\": 10, \"max_batch_timeout\": 5 }\n```\n\n### 5. Queue Consumer Routing (`api/src/index.ts`)\n\nAdd new branch in `queue()` handler at line ~193, before the unknown-message fallback:\n\n```typescript\n} else if (firstMessage && isSearchIndexMessage(firstMessage)) {\n  await processSearchIndexBatch(\n    batch as MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\n    env,\n  );\n}\n```\n\nImport `SearchIndexMessage`, `isSearchIndexMessage`, `processSearchIndexBatch` from `../lib/search-index-queue`.\n\n### 6. Enqueue in Webhook Processing (`api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts`)\n\n**In `processSessionsPushEvent()`** — after line 965 (`db.checkpoints.upsertBatch` succeeds):\n```typescript\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\n    checkpointIds,\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\n}\n```\n\n**In `processCommitPushEvent()`** — after line 1220 (`db.checkpoints.upsertCommitBatch` succeeds):\n```typescript\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\n    checkpointIds: checkpointCommits.map((c) => c.checkpointId),\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\n}\n```\n\nBoth are guarded by `env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` — if the binding isn't configured, webhook processing is unaffected. The `send()` call is fast (queue is local to the worker) and non-blocking to the webhook response.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n- **Optional everything**: Queue 